What will you be wearing on Christmas Day?🎄

Ever since I was a child, my family always dressed up for both Christmas Eve and Christmas Day…we may not have had all the money in the world, but you would never know that from looking at us!  My sister, mother and I wore combinations of black velvet, red plaid, and satin blouses…my father wore a jacket and tie, dress pants, and cordovan loafers…

I remember as a new bride in my 20s, being astounded (actually horrified) that my husband’s family wore jeans and sneakers on Christmas Day! 😳 It seemed so wrong! At the age of 64, I now recognize that there really is no right or wrong, we all learn different ‘rules’ as we grow up. Values and expectations are not the same for all of us…

As you decide what to wear tonight or tomorrow, the bottom line is what makes you feel good, what puts a smile on your face…as for me, I will stick with dressing up. 😊

Merry Christmas everyone! ❤️

Life is good when you put on a swimsuit in the morning, and wear nothing else until it’s time to dress for dinner! 😜

On our recent vacay to @turksandcaicos_official, here is a look at some of the swimsuits I wore…🌴

@oneoneswim…so far I have this in aqua and in red, with a purple one on the way…super flattering and very comfortable!  I take a large top and medium bottom. It did take some time for me to get comfortable with my ass exposed, but that is completely the norm these days - for ALL shapes, all sizes, and regardless of your AGE! 😜

The green bikini is by @bambaswim…well made but very skimpy on the bottom! Drink tequila and you no longer notice…🍹

The snakeskin bikini is by @camillawithlove, found a few years ago at a hotel gift shop…its a great print that is easily styled with cowboy hats and boho jewelry…🤠

Black/tan/white bikini is by @vix_global … looks more naughty than it is because of the color blocking! I wear a black cotton halter minidress as a coverup…well-made and comfortable. ☀️

White one-shoulder bikini is by @solidandstriped…this kind of two-piece you could easily wear with your grandkids - full coverage bottom. 

Finally, hubby in a flamingo print suit by @chubbies that was a Christmas gift from my sister! 🦩

FYI: 

🌴Buying swimsuits online is possible as long as the brand allows returns and/or exchanges. 

🌴Pay close attention to the location of the brand; sometimes the cost of shipping is as much as the swimsuit!

Another example of serious style! 

As much as I love bold, standout, and sexy styles, when it comes to certain situations I strongly believe in a more conservative approach. It is a sign of respect for the event and it sends a message of integrity and credibility. 

Some rules of thumb for serious style: 

- Stick to neutrals for the most part; add a bright color as an accent piece rather than head to toe. 

- Avoid ruffles and ruching! Tailored styles say that you mean business. 

- High heels are perfectly ok in classic looks; avoid ankle straps, platforms, or open toed shoes. 

- Accessorize minimally.  If you choose to wear a statement earring or necklace, tone down your other accessories. 

My serious outfit: an old Theory sheath dress, a butterscotch velvet blazer @circolo_1901, a statement necklace by @frenchkandejewelry, and killer shoes by @ralphlauren. 

One day a crop top, one day a sheath dress! This is 65. 😜

- Sporty/athletic 
- Elegant/glam
- Sexy/fun
- Feminine/demure

No big surprise, I like sexy/fun styles the most…as much as I admire sophisticated one piece suits, it seems that they are for lounging poolside with a wide-brimmed hat, while drinking Evian water or a wine spritzer…I am generally up and about on the beach, hair blowing in the wind, drinking tequila! 😆

More of my beach style faves:

- Always jewelry; lots of bracelets, big hoop earrings, and a necklace or two. 
- Cowboy hats! 
- Cover-ups that cover top and bottom so I am ‘decent’ walking through the hotel or sitting at breakfast. 😊
- Beach shoes with a heel. 
- Stylish sunnies!

Business casual, my way! 😃

As I reflect on my business casual style through 2023, I definitely see a pattern in what I like best…

- Leather.  Whether faux or real, I love it all! It adds texture and edginess, and works year round. (These pants by @jcrew)

- Mixing looks.  Head to toe ‘corporate’ can look very dated; it’s way more interesting to mix conservative pieces with something fun and/or casual. (Such as this combo - black wool blazer with white tee by @ragandbone) 

- Neutrals. Never do I tire of navy, cream, or black; my favorite color combo is black, camel, and white. Classic and classy. 

- Bold accessories.  Whether it’s layered necklaces, an arm of bracelets, a statement belt, a scarf or a hat, they all create a look that’s uniquely you.  My beret says it all! 

- Heels. You won’t find me in six-inch stilettos at work, but you will never find me in flats. I find three-inch heels perfect for daytime;  these booties by @ragandbone. 

And finally…
